nodes.body:
Here are the [benchmark results](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/run-detail/3d026d13-fc5f-4681-addd-fccddf15cd55) for commit 8523584c431fa717991340c21aa6c29c9233ad78.
There were [significant changes](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/compare/89242818-c6af-4303-a830-0446dfe955ee/to/3d026d13-fc5f-4681-addd-fccddf15cd55) against commit 2523a65bd2b94019a3afb291e9499abcaa0f7c0a:
```diff
  Benchmark                                                   Metric           Change
  ===================================================================================
- build                                                       initialization     5.1%
+ build                                                       linting          -23.9%
- lint                                                        wall-clock         5.3%
+ ~Mathlib.Algebra.Homology.DifferentialObject                instructions      -6.9%
+ ~Mathlib.Algebra.Order.Group.PosPart                        instructions     -44.1%
- ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Abelian.InjectiveResolution         instructions       9.0%
- ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Limits.Final                        instructions       8.3%
- ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Monoidal.Internal.FunctorCategory   instructions       7.1%
- ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Monoidal.Mod_                       instructions       9.2%
- ~Mathlib.Combinatorics.SimpleGraph.Operations               instructions     544.9%
+ ~Mathlib.RepresentationTheory.Action.Basic                  instructions      -2.5%
- ~Mathlib.RepresentationTheory.Character                     instructions      29.7%
```
I think this was run against the wrong version of mathlib so the results are mixed, but I think the -23% linting time is good news.
